tip.text: For those curious to know what the train has for food..
Be warned! You need patience in waiting for your order (from juice to water to appetizers to main course)... Even deserts (though it's so stale n not fresh!).... They could really test your patience
Butter chicken! Not the best but definitely more enjoyable compared to all the other North Indian Restaurants in Malaysia! (Ps. The best creamiest butter chicken has to be in Singapore Moghul Mahal)
Tawa Mutton! (Another dish worth trying for those who are bored of the usual rogan josh).
Shimla Mirch Aloo! (Worth a try for those who are bored of the usual aloo dishes like aloo gobi, aloo jeera and etc etc).

Dhal Tadka! One of the better yellow dhal among all North Indian restaurants in Malaysia... It brings back faith into yellow dhal for those who hate it. Give yourself a chance to enjoy yellow dhal. :)
Do try the 'Fish Achari'...it's boneless fish cubes cooked in tandoori style with pickled spices! Deffinitely a not to be missed!
Please avoid ghajar la halwa! Smells n taste so stale! Definitely not cooked fresh..unless u love food poisoning.. Then be my guest
Train derailed @ Kulai... So no train services back to Singapore from 27th till 2nd feb 2013.
A few pointers for u all...
